==English==

===Noun===
{{en-noun-reg}}
# A [[defect]]; something that [[detract]]s from [[perfection]]
# A [[mistake]] or [[error]]
# A [[weakness]] of [[character]]
# A [[minor]] [[offense]]
# [[Blame]]; the [[responsibility]] for a mistake
# (Geology) A [[fracture]] in a [[rock]] [[formation]] causing a [[discontinuity]]
# (Tennis) An [[illegal]] [[serve]]

====Translations====
*French: [[défaut]] {{m}} (1,3), [[faute]] {{f}} (2, 4, 5, 7), [[faille]] {{f}} (6)

===Verb===
{{en-infl-reg-consonant|fault||}}
# ''([[transitive]]):'' To [[criticize]], [[blame]] or find fault with something or someone.
# ''([[intransitive]], Geology):'' To fracture.
# ''([[intransitive]]):'' To [[commit]] a mistake or error.

====Translations====
*French: [[mettre]] en [[défaut]] (1), [[trouver]] une [[faille]] dans (1), se [[failler]] (2), [[faillir]] (3)

===Related terms===
* [[to a fault]] - to an excessive degree

